Lots of food for the price but I gave 1 star for the following:  We had bad service. The woman who took our order apparently spoke no English. Instead of getting someone who does, she attempts to take our order (which takes forever due to the language barrier). She then calls someone who DOES speak some English over to verify the order that she has taken from us - which needed some editing. After about 10 minutes, we finally have our order in.  My friend asks for Dr. Pepper, the woman says okay and leaves - never returns with a drink. Turns out they don't have Dr. Pepper so the server just didn't bring her anything or even let her know they didn't have it. So she calls another server to the table to ask for a Coke, "diet Coke?" Is the response she gets. "No, Coke. Regular Coke" - the woman leaves, confused, but comes back with a Coke after several minutes.  Our food comes within probably 15-20 minutes. The order is correct. We start eating. Meanwhile, a large family taking up two 8 person tables is seated not far from us. A child within that family starts smacking chopsticks on his plate, very loudly, and for a very long time. Almost the entirety of our meal, actually. Several servers went to that table for various things and let the disruption continue for at least 20-25 minutes. The only reason is stopped is because their food came.  Every bit of this is bad service, in my opinion. I did not leave a tip. I wrote "None" on the tip line to be clear that it was not an accident. The woman who came to collect our signed receipts confronted my friend and asked why he wasn't leaving a tip. Mind you, our bills were separate and he HAD left a very small tip because he ALSO was unhappy with the experience. She instantly got an attitude and snapped "I work hard" and "why you no leave something for us?" To which I responded "if I'm being honest, I think the service was bad and it's absolutely inappropriate to DEMAND a tip that was not given to you for a reason". She mumbled something, I responded "you don't have to worry, I won't be returning" and she stormed off.  So, I think if you want to order food from here for take out, it's probably worth it. The food WAS good and I did get A LOT (will attach picture - chicken chow mein) but if you're a person that cares about customer service find somewhere else to dine in.

Pretty standard Chinese food. Haven't been here for years and it hasn't changed much. Friendly service and the food comes out pretty quick. The prices are very reasonable for the portion of food. The restaurant is on the second floor of the building. Interior is standard for a Chinese restaurant.  We decided to get the set dinner meal for like 10 people. It comes with a good mix of food to satisfy everyone's craving. The food was pretty standard and not too greasy. The family set menu also comes with some soup before the meal and red bean soup for dessert. Both are pretty standard for a Chinese dinner.

We love coming back here to celebrate Birthdays, mothers day, fathers day, anniversaries , any occasions or whenever we crave for it. Eventhough we live in the suburbs we just cant find such place that has the foods that will make you come back for more. Service is amazing. Altho there are times we get disappointed by some of the foods we used to order cuz it doesnt taste like it used to. Overall I highly recommend this place for any events that you guys would love to celebrate.

This restaurant need to train their staff, we had a late lunch at this restaurant on September 19th. From the time we arrived and requested a table for 4, the waiter was already having an attitude, it became worse when we asked for a oolong tea, he gave us jasmin tea and argued that they never serve oolong tea and turns his back on us. We proceed to order our food and he still has an attitude, but we tried to be nice to him. He first served the soup but he bangs the soup bowls and spoons so i volunteered to serve the soup my self. We asked for water and bangs glasses infront of us. The japanese tofu we ordered is so salty as was the salt and pepper smelt fish; it looks like they rolled these foods in salt.  We asked  to replace it, he just take take the food and turns his back and when hes about to enter the kitchen he shouted if we're going to cancel the food or we want replacement. We did ask for replacement but he still does the same thing when he serves us the food. We asked for his name and turns his back to us and shouted "Jose".  When we're done with our meal, I decided not to call his attention for the bill,  I went straight to the counter to pay. " By the way, this waiter who serves us have a snake or dragon tattoo on his arms".  In bill the server name is "Cola". Well, this is my worst experience in a restaurant in Chicago and i don't  recommend this restaurant..

What I love and hate about Orig. Trip. Crown is their lack of consistency. I've eaten there some days, particularly busy ones where the food is fresh and savory. It tasted properly stir fried with the right amount of seasoning and technique. However, I've also been more deeply disappointed on slow days when the dishes are just kind of very low quality and not fresh. The food just didn't seem as live. Well, that's to be expected of most restaurants.  I have really liked its following dishes: black pepper beef short ribs, deep fried whole flounder, salt & pepper shelled shrimp, red roasted quail or squab pigeons, tong choy w/ preserved tofu paste + jalapenos, tong choy w/ shrimp paste, yellow chives and cod fillet, fresh steamed oysters, and deep fried salt & pepper squid or calamari.
Bland and stale.  Weird aftertaste. Yuck. Huge portions though if you've just escaped from captivity and haven't eaten in a week.
